article.headline: Tennessee St. 69, E. Kentucky 63
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Parker Smith had 26 points and Jerrell Houston scored 11 points in the game's final 3 minutes to help Tennessee State beat Eastern Kentucky 69-63 on Saturday night. After Mike Rose pulled Eastern Kentucky within 56-55 by hitting one of two free throws with 3:18 remaining, Houston went on a spurt that also included a pair of rebounds to help put Tennessee State up 67-60 with 32 seconds left. Josh Taylor hit a 3-pointer to pull the Colonels (7-6, 1-2 Ohio Valley Conference) within four just 8 seconds later, but Houston grabbed a rebound to set up Gerald Robinson Jr.'s dunk that made it 69-63 and another board to seal the win with 2 seconds left. Robinson finished with 10 points for the Tigers (4-9, 2-1). Rose led the Colonels with 31 points and Taylor added 15. The Tigers shot 60 percent from the field (15 of 25) in the second half.
